# Backend Unit Tests

## Prerequisites

### 1. Navigate to the root directory
Make sure you are at the root of the project before doing anything else:
```
cd project-auto-suggestion-quiz
```


### 2. Install dependencies
```
pip3 install -r backend/requirements.txt
```
> This installs everything needed to run the backend and unit tests.

---

## Running Tests

From the root directory, run:
```
For Mac OS:
PYTHONPATH=. python3 -m pytest backend/backUnitTest/ -v

For Windows:
$env:PYTHONPATH="."
python -m pytest backend/backUnitTest/ -v
```


## Creating coverage
From the root directory, run:
```
PYTHONPATH=. python3 -m pytest backend/backUnitTest/ -v --cov=backend --cov-report=html

```

